The paper deals with the combinatorial and geometric properties of planar point sets, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves combinatorial arguments and graph theory, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of convexity is a fundamental topic in graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
